WEBVTT

00:00.300 --> 00:03.467
♪ WHEN THIS BOY
MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.467 --> 00:06.300
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.300 --> 00:11.300
♪ WANDERING DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:11.300 --> 00:12.467
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.467 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:18.867
♪ THAT WILL ALWAYS
STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.867 --> 00:23.133
♪ WHEN THIS BOY
MEETS WORLD ♪

00:24.900 --> 00:27.100
SHAWN AND ANGELA
ARE SO CUTE TOGETHER.

00:27.100 --> 00:29.367
MAYBE NEXT WEEKEND, THE
4 OF US COULD GO OUT--

00:29.367 --> 00:30.767
HA HA! "THE 4 OF US."

00:30.767 --> 00:32.000
WHAT?

00:32.000 --> 00:33.467
SHAWN'S 2-WEEK RULE.

00:33.467 --> 00:35.867
SO I GUESS THAT'S IT.
IT'S OVER.

00:35.867 --> 00:38.000
2 WEEKS. YOU KNEW THAT
GOING IN.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.100
I DID.

00:41.133 --> 00:43.400
WAIT. WHERE--
WHERE YOU GOING?

00:43.400 --> 00:44.500
OH, I'M SORRY.

00:44.500 --> 00:46.934
I THOUGHT YOU WERE DONE
LETTING ME DOWN EASY.

00:46.934 --> 00:48.200
GO AHEAD.

00:50.233 --> 00:51.767
NEVER MIND.

00:51.767 --> 00:54.100
ARE YOU OK?

00:54.100 --> 00:56.400
YOU'RE JUST
TAKING THIS SO WELL.

00:56.400 --> 00:59.867
IT WAS A GREAT
2 WEEKS. WE HAD FUN.

00:59.867 --> 01:02.767
YEAH. WE DID.

01:02.767 --> 01:04.667
SO?

01:04.667 --> 01:06.667
SO...

01:06.667 --> 01:08.200
SEE YA?

01:20.800 --> 01:22.567
THAT ANGELA'S
ALL RIGHT.

01:22.567 --> 01:24.500
I'M GONNA MISS
HER.

01:24.500 --> 01:27.300
WELL, THEN WHY DID YOU
BREAK UP WITH HER?

01:27.300 --> 01:29.767
AS THEY SAY
SOUTH OF
THE BORDER,

01:29.767 --> 01:31.033
<i>"DOS SEMANAS." </i>

01:31.033 --> 01:33.200
SHAWN, YOU GUYS WERE
REALLY GETTING ALONG!

01:33.200 --> 01:34.900
YOU KNOW, YOUR 2-WEEK
RULE IS DUMB.

01:34.900 --> 01:37.233
NO, NO, NO.
HIS ONE-WEEK RULE WAS DUMB.

01:37.233 --> 01:38.934
HIS 2-WEEK RULE
SHOWS GROWTH.

01:38.934 --> 01:39.934
SHAWN, JUST FACE IT.

01:39.934 --> 01:41.467
YOU'RE AFRAID
TO MAKE A COMMITMENT.

01:41.467 --> 01:42.600
I'M NOT AFRAID
TO MAKE A COMM--

01:42.600 --> 01:44.667
I'VE BEEN
WITH CORY
FOR 15 YEARS.

01:44.667 --> 01:46.967
YEAH. THEY'VE
BEEN GOOD YEARS.

01:46.967 --> 01:49.000
YOU WORKED
VERY HARD AT IT.

01:49.000 --> 01:50.000
HEY, IT TAKES 2.

01:50.000 --> 01:51.300
YOU KNOW WHAT,
CORY, I THINK--

01:51.300 --> 01:52.300
STOP!

01:52.300 --> 01:54.400
YOU'RE AFRAID
TO GET TO KNOW SOMEONE.

01:54.400 --> 01:56.734
YOU'RE AFRAID OF LETTING
SOMEONE GET TO KNOW YOU.

01:56.734 --> 01:58.033
AND UNLESS
YOU GET OVER THIS,

01:58.033 --> 01:59.033
YOU'RE GOING TO
GO THROUGH LIFE ALL ALONE

01:59.033 --> 02:00.233
EXCEPT FOR CORY,

02:00.233 --> 02:02.567
WHO WILL BRING YOU
MAGAZINES AND PUDDING.

02:02.567 --> 02:05.467
THERE. I THINK
I GOT THROUGH TO HIM.

02:07.500 --> 02:08.567
SURE, YOU DID, HONEY,

02:08.567 --> 02:11.400
AND NOW HE WANTS TO HEAR
WHAT SHE HAS TO SAY.

02:14.300 --> 02:15.400
HEY, WHAT
DID TOPANGA MEAN

02:15.400 --> 02:16.600
ABOUT ME BEING
AFRAID TO COMMIT?

02:16.600 --> 02:18.667
YOU KNOW,
MOST RELATIONSHIPS
DON'T WORK OUT,

02:18.667 --> 02:21.200
AND I JUST WANT
TO GET OUT BEFORE
ANYONE GETS HURT, OK?

02:21.200 --> 02:23.934
SHAWN, WE JUST WANT
YOU TO BE HAPPY.

02:23.934 --> 02:25.667
YEAH.

02:25.667 --> 02:28.467
HEY, LOOK. SOMEBODY
LEFT THEIR PURSE.

02:28.467 --> 02:30.700
HMM.

02:30.700 --> 02:32.867
HEY, MR. FEENY,
WE--WE FOUND
THIS PURSE.

02:32.867 --> 02:35.367
WHO RUNS THE
LOST AND FOUND?

02:37.500 --> 02:40.567
I DO, MR. MATTHEWS.

02:40.567 --> 02:44.000
I TEACH ENGLISH,
HISTORY, AND FILM,

02:44.000 --> 02:46.400
AND I RUN
THE LOST AND FOUND.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.300
WE'LL PUT UP A NOTICE.

02:48.300 --> 02:49.500
WOULD YOU?

02:50.600 --> 02:51.600
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
GO THROUGH IT

02:51.600 --> 02:52.934
AND SEE
IF THERE'S ANY I.D.

02:52.934 --> 02:55.834
NO. NOT GONNA.
I ONCE WENT THROUGH
MY MOM'S PURSE.

02:55.834 --> 02:58.000
YEAH. I CAN'T LOOK
AT HER ANYMORE.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.667
OK.

02:59.667 --> 03:00.800
STAND BACK.

03:00.800 --> 03:02.100
I'M GOING IN.

03:02.100 --> 03:03.700
AHEM. OK.
NO WALLET.

03:03.700 --> 03:04.867
NO I.D.

03:04.867 --> 03:06.233
WELL,
THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMETHING IN THERE

03:06.233 --> 03:08.300
THAT LETS US KNOW
WHO SHE IS, RIGHT?

03:08.300 --> 03:09.300
LIP GLOSS.

03:09.300 --> 03:12.667
SHE CARES
ABOUT HER LIPS.

03:13.967 --> 03:15.300
KIWI MANGO.

03:15.300 --> 03:16.500
NO WAY!

03:16.500 --> 03:18.467
KIWI MAN--
THAT IS SO SEXY!

03:18.467 --> 03:19.967
DO YOU KNOW
THAT THE TED KOPPEL SHOW

03:19.967 --> 03:23.767
CALLED THAT
"THE LIP GLOSS
OF FORBIDDEN LOVE"?

03:23.767 --> 03:26.000
HUH!
AND LOOK AT THIS.

03:26.000 --> 03:27.967
A BOOK OF SONNETS.

03:27.967 --> 03:30.400
AHA. SHAKESPEARE.
I HEAR HE'S GOOD.

03:30.400 --> 03:31.400
AND...

03:31.400 --> 03:33.367
NOTICE THE BOOKMARK.

03:33.367 --> 03:35.300
A TICKET STUB
TO A VAN DAMME MOVIE.

03:35.300 --> 03:37.233
ONLY THE GREATEST ACTOR
EVER MADE.

03:37.233 --> 03:39.000
OK, SO WHAT WE GOT HERE

03:39.000 --> 03:41.500
IS A PURSE-LOSING,
LIPS-PROTECTING,

03:41.500 --> 03:44.233
POETRY-READING,
VAN DAMME-LOVING GAL.

03:44.233 --> 03:45.600
WOW.

03:45.600 --> 03:48.000
I'D GIVE HER 2 WEEKS.

03:49.867 --> 03:52.000
MR. FEENY!

03:53.700 --> 03:55.300
WHAT IS IT,
MR. MATTHEWS?

03:55.300 --> 03:58.133
CRISIS AT COLLEGE.
I HAVE A REALLY BIG TEST, OK?

03:58.133 --> 03:59.734
AND TEST SCORES
ARE IMPORTANT IN COLLEGE.

03:59.734 --> 04:02.100
IT TURNS OUT THEY BASE
ALL THE GRADES ON THEM.

04:02.100 --> 04:04.500
SO LET'S
GET CRACKING, OK?

04:04.500 --> 04:05.500
ERIC,

04:05.500 --> 04:07.700
IT'S TIME YOU DID
THIS ON YOUR OWN.

04:07.700 --> 04:09.233
NOW, YOU'RE FINE.

04:09.233 --> 04:11.900
YOU HAVE
ALL THE SKILLS.

04:11.900 --> 04:13.367
HEY...

04:13.367 --> 04:16.400
YOU'RE TUTORING
ANOTHER STUDENT IN THERE,
AREN'T YOU?

04:19.767 --> 04:21.100
I'M SURE
I DON'T KNOW

04:21.100 --> 04:23.600
WHAT YOU'RE
TALKING ABOUT.

04:23.600 --> 04:24.867
IT'S KEVIN McDOUGAL,
ISN'T IT?

04:24.867 --> 04:27.734
THE KID
FROM THE OTHER SIDE.

04:27.734 --> 04:29.900
ERIC,
YOU HAVE THE ABILITY

04:29.900 --> 04:30.900
TO DO FINE.

04:30.900 --> 04:33.000
NOW, JUST...
STUDY THE MATERIALS.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.467
I HAVE CONFIDENCE
IN YOU.

04:35.467 --> 04:38.033
I JUST WISH
YOU HAD CONFIDENCE
IN YOURSELF.

04:38.033 --> 04:40.400
GOOD LUCK, MY BOY.

04:42.200 --> 04:44.767
HE'S A PROFESSIONAL TUTOR!

04:44.767 --> 04:47.500
YOU MEAN NOTHING TO HIM!

04:48.800 --> 04:50.400
ALL RIGHT.
HERE'S AN EASY ONE:

04:50.400 --> 04:51.400
THE LOUISIANA PURCHASE?

04:51.400 --> 04:52.400
I DON'T KNOW!

04:52.400 --> 04:55.400
STOP HOUNDING ME!

04:55.400 --> 04:57.600
COME ON, MAN!

04:57.600 --> 04:59.400
2 GUYS?

04:59.400 --> 05:01.033
1800s?

05:01.033 --> 05:03.033
LEWIS AND...

05:03.033 --> 05:05.867
LEWIS.

05:05.867 --> 05:08.033
THE LEWIS TWINS.

05:08.033 --> 05:09.600
OH, MAN,
WHO AM I KIDDING?

05:09.600 --> 05:11.600
I DON'T BELONG
IN COLLEGE.

05:11.600 --> 05:13.000
LOOK, JUST HIT THE BOOKS
A LITTLE HARDER.

05:13.000 --> 05:14.667
I'LL BE BACK, AND
WE'LL TRY IT AGAIN, OK?

05:14.667 --> 05:15.867
ALL RIGHT.

05:15.867 --> 05:18.233
COME ON, ERIC,
YOU CAN DO THIS.

05:18.233 --> 05:21.500
JUST RELAX
AND FOCUS.

05:21.500 --> 05:23.100
COLUMBUS...

05:23.100 --> 05:25.000
CORTéS.

05:25.000 --> 05:27.000
UH, MARCO...

05:28.300 --> 05:29.600
COME ON.

05:29.600 --> 05:31.800
MARCO...

05:31.800 --> 05:35.400
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS! MARCO...

05:35.400 --> 05:38.000
Mr. Feeny: POLO.

05:42.367 --> 05:44.467
MARCO...

05:44.467 --> 05:46.033
POLO.

05:47.600 --> 05:49.033
WHA--

05:49.033 --> 05:51.300
MR. FEENY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

05:51.300 --> 05:53.734
I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.

05:53.734 --> 05:54.967
WHO'RE YOU TALKING TO?

05:54.967 --> 05:58.567
OH, JACK, RIGHT.
YOU REMEMBER
MY MENTOR MR. FEENY.

05:58.567 --> 06:00.467
YES, I DO.

06:00.467 --> 06:02.734
WHO'RE YOU
TALKING TO?

06:02.734 --> 06:04.834
UH, MR. FEENY.

06:04.834 --> 06:07.367
THE BRITISH GUY
ON OUR COUCH
RIGHT THERE.

06:07.367 --> 06:11.767
I'M FROM BOSTON,
YOU BOOB.

06:11.767 --> 06:14.467
UH, EXCUSE ME.
A LITTLE RESPECT.

06:14.467 --> 06:16.367
YOU'RE A GUEST
IN MY HOUSE.

06:16.367 --> 06:19.400
UH, EXCUSE ME.
I PAY RENT HERE.

06:19.400 --> 06:21.467
I'M TALKING
TO MR. FEENY.

06:21.467 --> 06:22.500
OH.

06:22.500 --> 06:23.967
YOUR MENTOR.

06:23.967 --> 06:25.734
YEAH.

06:25.734 --> 06:28.100
ON THE COUCH.

06:29.133 --> 06:30.367
MISTER--THE GUY!

06:30.367 --> 06:33.734
RIGHT THERE! ON
OUR COUCH! EATING
OUR BEER NUTS!

06:33.734 --> 06:35.667
MMM. NUTTY.

06:37.467 --> 06:39.600
OK, I'M LEAVING.

06:39.600 --> 06:42.367
MAN,
DID I PICK A RUDIE
FOR A ROOMMATE.

06:42.367 --> 06:44.734
HE ACTS LIKE YOU
DON'T EVEN EXIST.

06:44.734 --> 06:46.967
HE CAN'T SEE ME.

06:46.967 --> 06:48.700
ONLY YOU CAN SEE ME.

06:48.700 --> 06:49.900
AND ONLY YOU CAN SEE ME

06:49.900 --> 06:53.200
BECAUSE I EXIST ONLY
IN YOUR IMAGINATION.

06:53.200 --> 06:55.934
OK. SO WHY
ARE YOU HERE?

06:58.300 --> 06:59.700
TO TAKE YOU
TO THE LIBRARY.

06:59.700 --> 07:01.700
YOU NEED TO STUDY,
AND I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.

07:01.700 --> 07:02.734
THAT MAKES SENSE.

07:02.734 --> 07:04.300
CAN YOU JUST
HANG ON ONE SECOND?

07:04.300 --> 07:05.700
JACK?

07:05.700 --> 07:06.700
YEAH.

07:06.700 --> 07:07.934
HEY, BUDDY,
QUICK QUESTION:

07:07.934 --> 07:10.567
FEENY OR NO FEENY?

07:10.567 --> 07:12.200
NO FEENY.

07:12.200 --> 07:13.200
THANK YOU.

07:13.200 --> 07:16.000
YOU READY?
I'M DRIVING.
COME ON.

07:17.033 --> 07:18.033
HEY.

07:18.033 --> 07:19.734
ANYONE CALL
ABOUT THAT PURSE YET?

07:19.734 --> 07:22.400
"LOVE IS NOT LOVE
WHICH ALTERS

07:22.400 --> 07:24.300
"WHEN IT
ALTERATION FINDS

07:24.300 --> 07:27.400
OR BENDS
WITH THE REMOVER
TO REMOVE."

07:27.400 --> 07:29.500
NO ONE CALLED, HUH?
BUMMER.

07:29.500 --> 07:30.700
ANYWAY, LISTEN.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.967
TOPANGA AND I
WERE TALKING
ABOUT YOUR PROBLEM.

07:32.967 --> 07:34.233
I DON'T
HAVE A PROBLEM.

07:34.233 --> 07:36.567
WE FEEL THAT IF YOU
MET THE RIGHT GIRL--

07:36.567 --> 07:37.667
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

07:37.667 --> 07:40.000
IS THIS YOU
OR TOPANGA TALKING?

07:40.000 --> 07:41.900
SHE DECIDED
WE'RE ONE PERSON.

07:41.900 --> 07:43.033
ANYWAY,

07:43.033 --> 07:45.300
TOPANGA'S GOT
THIS FRIEND.
MM-HMM.

07:45.300 --> 07:46.300
DEBRA.

07:46.300 --> 07:47.467
NO. NO, NO, NO.

07:47.467 --> 07:48.600
I DON'T WANT
TO BE FIXED UP.

07:48.600 --> 07:50.567
HEY, YOU KNOW
WHAT ELSE I FOUND
IN THIS PURSE?

07:50.567 --> 07:54.000
A GUITAR PICK,
A GREENPEACE
STICKER,

07:54.000 --> 07:55.200
AND A BOX
OF SNO-CAPS,

07:55.200 --> 07:57.600
ONLY THE GREATEST
MOVIE SNACK
EVER MADE.

07:57.600 --> 07:59.200
WAIT A MINUTE. SHAWN.

07:59.200 --> 08:02.000
LISTEN. DON'T YOU
WANT THAT FEELING?

08:02.000 --> 08:03.000
WHAT FEELING?

08:03.000 --> 08:04.700
YOU KNOW,
THAT FEELING YOU GET

08:04.700 --> 08:06.200
WHEN YOU MEET
SOMEONE SPECIAL.

08:06.200 --> 08:09.233
IT'S THE FEELING
I GET EVERY DAY
WHEN I'M WITH TOPANGA.

08:09.233 --> 08:13.600
YOU KNOW, IT'S--
IT'S WARM AND HAPPY
AND FUZZY...

08:13.600 --> 08:17.867
I--I CAN'T DESCRIBE IT,
BUT THERE ARE BUNNIES...

08:17.867 --> 08:19.567
LOTS OF BUNNIES.

08:19.567 --> 08:24.000
YOU KNOW, WE--WE
JUST WANT YOU TO
HAVE THAT FEELING.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.567
OK?

08:25.567 --> 08:26.767
SO MEET DEBBIE.

08:26.767 --> 08:27.767
FINE.

08:27.767 --> 08:29.300
I'LL MEET DEBBIE.

08:29.300 --> 08:31.500
GOOD.

08:36.500 --> 08:40.700
[VIVALDI'S <i>4 SEASONS PLAYING] </i>

08:40.700 --> 08:43.200
I WONDER IF
DEBBIE'S ANYTHING
LIKE THIS GIRL.

08:43.200 --> 08:44.200
WHAT GIRL?

08:44.200 --> 08:45.300
THE PURSE GIRL.

08:45.300 --> 08:47.300
DID YOU KNOW
THAT SHE LIKES
CLASSICAL MUSIC?

08:47.300 --> 08:49.367
SHAWN, YOU HATE
CLASSICAL MUSIC.

08:49.367 --> 08:51.033
WELL, I JUST NEVER
GAVE IT A CHANCE.

08:51.033 --> 08:53.500
THIS IS
THE PART WHERE
THE VIOLINS ROCK!

08:53.500 --> 08:54.500
[MUSIC UP]

08:54.500 --> 08:56.100
[VIOLIN PLAYING]

08:57.600 --> 09:01.033
SHAWN, SHAWN,
PLEASE DON'T.
DON'T. DON'T.

09:01.033 --> 09:02.767
DON'T DO THIS, OK?

09:02.767 --> 09:04.000
BECAUSE
YOUR DATE DEBBIE

09:04.000 --> 09:06.400
IS UNDER
THE IMPRESSION
THAT YOU DON'T DO...

09:06.400 --> 09:07.967
THIS.

09:07.967 --> 09:09.767
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

09:09.767 --> 09:11.500
OK.

09:13.100 --> 09:15.900
HELLO, LADIES.
HELLO, HELLO. HI.

09:15.900 --> 09:17.767
AND DEBBIE,
HOW ARE YOU?

09:17.767 --> 09:18.767
HI.

09:18.767 --> 09:19.834
I'M CORY,

09:19.834 --> 09:21.600
AND THIS IS
MY BEST FRIEND
SHAWN HUNTER.

09:21.600 --> 09:23.900
YOU'RE VERY THIN!

09:25.767 --> 09:27.100
IS THAT BAD?

09:27.100 --> 09:28.667
OH, NO! IT'S GOOD.

09:28.667 --> 09:30.100
LOW IMPACT,
HIGH IMPACT,

09:30.100 --> 09:31.800
KICKBOXING,
CROSS TRAINING.

09:31.800 --> 09:32.967
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

09:32.967 --> 09:35.400
BECAUSE WHATEVER IT IS,
IT'S WORKING.

09:35.400 --> 09:38.767
I EAT A LOT
OF BURGERS.

09:38.767 --> 09:40.100
GOOD! GOOD!

09:40.100 --> 09:42.600
EAT FAT TO BURN FAT.

09:42.600 --> 09:44.400
DEBBIE IS
AN AEROBICS
INSTRUCTOR!

09:44.400 --> 09:45.567
REALLY!
NO!

09:45.567 --> 09:46.767
EXCELLENT,
EXCELLENT!
THAT'S
FANTASTIC!

09:46.767 --> 09:48.834
EXCELLENT!
THIS IS GOOD!
WHAT?

09:48.834 --> 09:50.000
WHY WOULD YOU THINK

09:50.000 --> 09:51.800
THAT THIS GIRL
IS FOR ME?

09:51.800 --> 09:52.800
WORD AROUND THE GYM:

09:52.800 --> 09:54.834
SHAWN HUNTER
IS QUITE A KISSER.

09:54.834 --> 09:55.967
OH...

09:58.200 --> 09:59.867
THIS COULD WORK.
THEY SEEM RIGHT
FOR EACH OTHER.

09:59.867 --> 10:00.867
I DON'T KNOW.

10:00.867 --> 10:02.200
SHAWN DOESN'T SWEAT
THAT MUCH.

10:02.200 --> 10:04.100
I HOPE
SHE'S OK WITH THAT.

10:04.100 --> 10:06.600
WHY--WHY DON'T
WE TALK FIRST?

10:06.600 --> 10:07.600
[VIVALDI PLAYING]

10:07.600 --> 10:10.300
UM, WHAT KIND OF
MUSIC DO YOU LIKE?

10:11.600 --> 10:12.600
NOT THIS.

10:12.600 --> 10:14.700
YOU CAN'T WORK OUT
TO THIS.

10:14.700 --> 10:15.700
I LIKE IT.

10:15.700 --> 10:17.700
DEBBIE, IF YOU
CLOSE YOUR EYES,

10:17.700 --> 10:20.100
YOU CAN ACTUALLY
SEE SPRING,

10:20.100 --> 10:22.500
ANIMALS
AWAKENING FROM
THEIR WINTER REST,

10:22.500 --> 10:25.000
FLOWERS BLOSSOMING
INTO FULL BLOOM.

10:25.000 --> 10:26.467
TRY IT.

10:28.600 --> 10:33.500
I JUST SEE
FAT PEOPLE BOUNCING.

10:33.500 --> 10:35.900
I THINK THERE'S
A RELATIONSHIP
HAPPENING HERE.

10:35.900 --> 10:37.367
WELL, LET US GO TO
OUR NEW COUPLE FRIENDS

10:37.367 --> 10:41.033
AND MAKE PLANS
FOR WEEKENDS AT
THE COTTAGE, HMM?

10:41.033 --> 10:45.200
"LOVE IS NOT LOVE
WHICH ALTERS

10:45.200 --> 10:47.200
"WHEN IT ALTERATION
FINDS

10:47.200 --> 10:49.300
OHH.
"OR BENDS
WITH THE REMOVER

10:49.300 --> 10:50.300
TO REMOVE."

10:50.300 --> 10:53.467
WHY ARE YOU
DOING THIS TO ME?

10:53.467 --> 10:55.667
HI! HOW'S
THE HAPPY COUPLE DOING?

10:55.667 --> 10:56.667
[MUSIC STOPS]

10:56.667 --> 10:58.834
I NEED CHOCOLATE.

10:58.834 --> 11:01.967
THAT'S 14 GRAMS OF FAT.

11:01.967 --> 11:03.667
AND YOU HAVE A PURSE.

11:03.667 --> 11:04.700
YES, I DO.

11:04.700 --> 11:05.934
OH, COME ON NOW.

11:05.934 --> 11:07.767
THAT--THAT'S NOT
REALLY HIS PURSE.

11:07.767 --> 11:08.767
UH...

11:08.767 --> 11:10.400
HE FOUND THAT PURSE.

11:10.400 --> 11:12.967
OH? WELL, HE FOUND
AN UGLY ONE.

11:12.967 --> 11:13.967
HEY.

11:13.967 --> 11:16.600
I HAPPEN TO LIKE
THIS PURSE.

11:16.600 --> 11:19.033
TOPANGA, I DON'T THINK
THIS IS WORKING.

11:19.033 --> 11:20.367
DEBBIE, GIVE IT
A CHANCE.

11:20.367 --> 11:23.400
NO, NO,
LOOK, UM...

11:23.400 --> 11:26.233
I CAN'T
DO THIS, OK?
DON'T FIX ME UP.

11:26.233 --> 11:27.233
SHAWN.

11:27.233 --> 11:28.367
NO. YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:28.367 --> 11:31.800
I AM PERFECTLY HAPPY
WITH THE WAY THINGS ARE.

11:38.300 --> 11:40.600
[HUMMING VIVALDI]

11:40.600 --> 11:41.600
HEY.

11:41.600 --> 11:42.967
HEY.

11:42.967 --> 11:43.967
LISTEN, UH,

11:43.967 --> 11:46.100
SORRY ABOUT
LAST NIGHT.

11:46.100 --> 11:47.900
ON PAPER
DEBBIE SOUNDED
PRETTY GOOD.

11:47.900 --> 11:49.500
OH. OH,
FORGET ABOUT IT.

11:49.500 --> 11:50.500
HERE.

11:50.500 --> 11:52.033
HAVE A SNO-CAP.

11:52.033 --> 11:53.033
HEY, SHAWN.

11:53.033 --> 11:54.033
HEY, ANGELA.

11:54.033 --> 11:56.467
SOMETHING'S
DIFFERENT ABOUT YOU.

11:56.467 --> 11:58.000
WHAT IS THAT,
A NEW SHIRT?

11:58.000 --> 12:01.200
THIS OLD THING?
NO. STOP.

12:01.200 --> 12:02.500
WELL, IT WORKS
FOR YOU.

12:02.500 --> 12:04.700
THANKS. THANKS.

12:06.000 --> 12:07.400
BYE.

12:10.500 --> 12:13.400
OK, WHY ARE
YOU SO HAPPY?

12:13.400 --> 12:15.600
WELL, I, UH...

12:15.600 --> 12:17.300
I THINK
I MET SOMEONE.

12:17.300 --> 12:18.700
SOMEONE...

12:18.700 --> 12:19.700
SPECIAL.

12:19.700 --> 12:23.033
HEE HEE HEE!

12:23.033 --> 12:24.400
SHAWN,
YOU JUST GIGGLED.

12:24.400 --> 12:26.367
YEAH. I'VE BEEN
DOING THAT A LOT.

12:26.367 --> 12:27.600
HEE HEE HEE! OK.

12:27.600 --> 12:28.867
I HAVE THE FEELING,
CORY.

12:28.867 --> 12:31.100
DO YOU KNOW THE ONE
THAT YOU WERE TRYING
TO EXPLAIN?

12:31.100 --> 12:32.400
WELL, I WOKE UP
THIS MORNING,

12:32.400 --> 12:35.300
AND IT WAS LIKE RAYS
OF SUNSHINE WERE--

12:35.300 --> 12:36.700
NO, NO, NO, NO.

12:36.700 --> 12:40.033
IT WAS MORE LIKE FLUFFY,
MARSHMALLOW CLOUDS
COATED IN SYRUP--

12:40.033 --> 12:42.300
NO. I--I CAN'T
EXPLAIN IT EITHER,

12:42.300 --> 12:44.033
BUT I THOUGHT
I SAW A BUNNY.

12:44.033 --> 12:46.033
WELL,
GOOD FOR YOU, SHAWN.

12:46.033 --> 12:47.667
SO WHO IS IT?

12:47.667 --> 12:49.600
IT'S HER.

12:50.667 --> 12:52.834
THE PURSE GIRL.

12:52.834 --> 12:55.300
SHAWN,
YOU DON'T KNOW HER.

12:55.300 --> 12:57.233
CORY...

12:58.400 --> 13:00.200
I DO KNOW THIS GIRL.

13:00.200 --> 13:03.734
LOOK, I--I KNOW
EVERYTHING ABOUT HER.

13:03.734 --> 13:05.834
I'M IN LOVE.

13:05.834 --> 13:07.700
WELL, HEY,
I HOPE YOU FIND HER.

13:07.700 --> 13:10.700
IT'S LIKE
YOU AND TOPANGA,
YOU KNOW?

13:10.700 --> 13:11.967
A PERFECT FIT.

13:11.967 --> 13:13.934
YEAH, BUT I DIDN'T
FALL IN LOVE

13:13.934 --> 13:15.400
WITH HER LUGGAGE.

13:19.500 --> 13:20.500
"B"!

13:20.500 --> 13:22.200
A "B" IN COLLEGE
IS LIKE...

13:22.200 --> 13:24.500
THE BEST YOU CAN DO!

13:24.500 --> 13:26.700
YOU DID VERY WELL,
ERIC.

13:26.700 --> 13:28.834
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

13:30.300 --> 13:32.100
HELLO.

13:34.000 --> 13:35.467
YOU KNOW,
A LOT OF PEOPLE

13:35.467 --> 13:37.300
MIGHT NOT APPRECIATE
WHAT YOU DO,

13:37.300 --> 13:39.367
BUT, UH...I DO.

13:43.600 --> 13:45.133
YOU KNOW, MR. MATTHEWS,

13:45.133 --> 13:48.133
I UNDERSTAND THAT
I'M IN YOUR IMAGINATION,

13:48.133 --> 13:50.400
BUT THIS...ASCOT...

13:50.400 --> 13:52.000
I THINK
WE CAN DO BETTER.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.767
I'LL DO ANYTHING
YOU WANT.

13:55.767 --> 13:58.834
AND LOOK HERE,
YOU'VE GOT ME IN BRIEFS.

13:58.834 --> 14:00.400
I'M A BOXER MAN.

14:00.400 --> 14:02.900
YOU WANT ME TO CHANGE
YOUR UNDERWEAR?

14:12.400 --> 14:13.934
HEY, BUDDY!

14:13.934 --> 14:17.767
I'M WAVING A "B"
IN HISTORY.

14:17.767 --> 14:19.800
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

14:20.900 --> 14:22.133
HOW DID YOU
GET A "B"?

14:22.133 --> 14:23.133
FEENY.

14:23.133 --> 14:24.133
THANKS.

14:24.133 --> 14:26.000
OH, RIGHT,
YOUR INVISIBLE
MENTOR GUY.

14:26.000 --> 14:28.567
COME ON, MAN, IF
YOU'VE GOT A SECRET,
LET ME IN ON IT.

14:28.567 --> 14:30.200
IT'S NO SECRET.
IT'S FEENY.

14:30.200 --> 14:32.500
UH, I BELIEVED IN HIM,
HE HELPED ME,

14:32.500 --> 14:34.667
I GOT A GOOD GRADE.

14:42.500 --> 14:45.600
MR...FEENY?

14:47.667 --> 14:51.100
MR. FEENY, ARE YOU
HERE, SIR?

14:51.100 --> 14:52.100
IT'S, UH...

14:52.100 --> 14:53.867
IT'S ME, JACK.

14:53.867 --> 14:55.467
ERIC'S FRIEND.

14:56.867 --> 14:58.934
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU'RE NOT MY MENTOR,

14:58.934 --> 15:02.233
BUT I JUST GOT BEAT
BY ERIC ON A TEST.

15:02.233 --> 15:04.367
THAT'S JUST PLAIN WRONG.

15:06.233 --> 15:07.233
SO...

15:07.233 --> 15:10.000
IF YOU COULD, SIR, BEGIN.

15:10.000 --> 15:11.767
I'M READY TO LEARN.

15:14.033 --> 15:15.467
JACK.

15:17.100 --> 15:18.800
HE'S NOT THERE.

15:18.800 --> 15:19.834
HE'S NOT?

15:19.834 --> 15:20.934
NO.

15:20.934 --> 15:23.033
HE'S
ON THE BALCONY.

15:28.500 --> 15:30.133
OH, SHAWNIE,
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.

15:30.133 --> 15:31.200
LISTEN, UM...

15:31.200 --> 15:32.800
BASED ON THE INFORMATION
WE'VE GATHERED

15:32.800 --> 15:34.200
FROM THE CONTENTS
OF THE PURSE,

15:34.200 --> 15:35.934
I PUT TOGETHER
A COMPOSITE DRAWING

15:35.934 --> 15:38.000
OF THE WOMAN
YOU LOVE.

15:39.100 --> 15:40.834
HUH? OK?

15:40.834 --> 15:42.600
OK, SHE'S GORGEOUS,

15:42.600 --> 15:43.600
BUT SHE'S SAD.

15:43.600 --> 15:46.400
SAD BECAUSE
SHE LOST HER PURSE.

15:47.467 --> 15:48.500
SHE, UH...

15:48.500 --> 15:49.800
AHEM. SHE CALLED.

15:49.800 --> 15:51.567
SHE SAW THE NOTICE
AND CALLED.

15:51.567 --> 15:54.000
THAT'S--THAT'S GREAT!
WHO IS IT? WHO IS IT?

15:54.000 --> 15:55.900
I DON'T KNOW.
JACK TOOK THE MESSAGE.

15:55.900 --> 15:57.734
I'M SUPPOSED TO MEET HER
AT CHUBBIE'S.

15:57.734 --> 15:59.567
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU
TAKE THIS WITH YOU

15:59.567 --> 16:02.467
TO MAKE SURE IT'S HER?

16:02.467 --> 16:03.900
I'M NOT GOING.

16:03.900 --> 16:05.767
YOU GO.

16:05.767 --> 16:07.567
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

16:08.600 --> 16:10.734
CORY, I--I
CAN'T MEET HER.

16:10.734 --> 16:12.000
THIS FEELING
IS SO INCREDIBLE,

16:12.000 --> 16:15.467
I JUST WANT TO HOLD
ON TO IT FOR AS LONG
AS POSSIBLE.

16:15.467 --> 16:19.867
I KNOW,
BUT DO YOU UNDERSTAND
THAT WHEN YOU MEET HER,

16:19.867 --> 16:21.600
THAT FEELING
WILL ONLY GET BETTER?

16:21.600 --> 16:22.967
AND--AND WHAT
IF IT DOESN'T?

16:22.967 --> 16:25.233
AND--AND WHAT IF
IT'S NOT AS GOOD
AS WHAT I HAVE NOW?

16:27.200 --> 16:29.200
WITH THE PURSE?

16:29.200 --> 16:31.100
JUST DROP IT, CORY.

16:31.100 --> 16:33.000
LISTEN, WHAT ARE YOU
SO AFRAID OF?

16:33.000 --> 16:34.900
I'M AFRAID
OF GETTING HURT, OK?

16:34.900 --> 16:37.100
I MEAN, I'VE SEEN
THE PAIN ON MY FATHER'S FACE

16:37.100 --> 16:40.734
EVERY TIME A WOMAN WALKS OUT
BECAUSE HE'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH.

16:40.734 --> 16:41.967
SHAWN.

16:41.967 --> 16:44.300
YOU ARE NOT
YOUR FATHER,

16:44.300 --> 16:45.300
OK?

16:45.300 --> 16:48.233
AND--AND THIS THING
IS NOT REAL!

16:48.233 --> 16:49.300
HI, GUYS.

16:49.300 --> 16:50.800
OH, HEY.

16:50.800 --> 16:52.367
THIS. THIS IS REAL,

16:52.367 --> 16:54.500
ALL RIGHT?
I SMILE AT HER,

16:54.500 --> 16:56.600
SHE SMILES BACK.
SHE'S THERE FOR ME.

16:56.600 --> 16:59.667
THROUGH THE GOOD
AND THE BAD.

16:59.667 --> 17:00.967
YEAH, WELL,
WHERE I COME FROM,

17:00.967 --> 17:03.033
I'VE NEVER SEEN LOVE WORK.

17:03.033 --> 17:05.200
BUT IT CAN. OK?

17:05.200 --> 17:08.033
THIS GIRL HERE
COULD BE YOUR LOVE,

17:08.033 --> 17:09.400
YOUR DESTINY.

17:10.500 --> 17:12.834
THAT WAS BEAUTIFUL,
CORY.

17:15.000 --> 17:17.600
WHAT IS THAT,
KIWI MANGO?

17:18.700 --> 17:20.800
IT'S VERY SEXY.

17:22.867 --> 17:26.467
WHITMAN. MAJOR WORK,
<i>LEAVES OF GRASS. </i>

17:26.467 --> 17:28.900
POE. MAJOR WORK,
<i>THE RAVEN. </i>

17:28.900 --> 17:30.500
QUOTH THE RAVEN...

17:30.500 --> 17:32.767
"NEVERMORE."

17:32.767 --> 17:34.000
MR. FEENY.
HMM?

17:34.000 --> 17:36.600
AREN'T YOU
A LITTLE OVERDRESSED
FOR THE LIBRARY?

17:36.600 --> 17:38.934
OH, NOT FOR THE ONE
IN LAUGHLIN, NEVADA.

17:38.934 --> 17:40.200
OOH, LAUGHLIN, NEVADA.

17:40.200 --> 17:43.734
POPULATION, 8,900.
MAJOR BUSINESS,
LEGALIZED GAMBLING,

17:43.734 --> 17:47.100
BIRTHPLACE OF
THE 2.99 PRIME RIB SPECIAL.

17:47.100 --> 17:49.133
WAIT, WHY ARE WE
GOING TO LAUGHLIN?

17:49.133 --> 17:51.700
<i>WE'RE </i>NOT GOING.
<i>I'M </i>GOING.

17:52.767 --> 17:53.767
WAIT A SECOND,
MR. FEENY,

17:53.767 --> 17:55.800
I CAN'T DO THIS
WITHOUT YOU.

17:55.800 --> 17:56.800
ERIC,

17:56.800 --> 17:59.500
YOU DID THIS
ALL ON YOUR OWN.

17:59.500 --> 18:01.400
YOU'VE ALWAYS
HAD THE SKILLS.

18:01.400 --> 18:03.033
JUST KEEP USING THEM,

18:03.033 --> 18:05.700
AND YOU'LL
NEVER BE WITHOUT ME.

18:05.700 --> 18:06.700
THAT'S WHAT YOU--

18:06.700 --> 18:09.133
THE REAL MR. FEENY--

18:09.133 --> 18:10.133
WOULD SAY.

18:10.133 --> 18:13.767
SMART MAN, THAT FEENY.

18:13.767 --> 18:14.767
OH, LOOK.

18:14.767 --> 18:15.934
A RARE BIRD.

18:15.934 --> 18:17.400
HUH?

18:20.767 --> 18:22.300
MARCO...

18:25.300 --> 18:27.400
[LOUDER]
MARCO...

18:30.834 --> 18:33.300
POLO,
MR. MATTHEWS.

18:39.934 --> 18:42.200
[VIVALDI PLAYING]

19:23.467 --> 19:24.467
HEY!

19:24.467 --> 19:25.600
DON'T EVER
TALK TO ME

19:25.600 --> 19:28.767
ABOUT LOVE OR
DESTINY AGAIN.

19:28.767 --> 19:29.767
UH, WHAT HAPPENED?

19:29.767 --> 19:31.934
I WENT THERE, OK?

19:31.934 --> 19:34.100
I PUT MY HEART
ON THE LINE.

19:34.100 --> 19:35.600
SHE'S GOT
A BOYFRIEND, CORY,

19:35.600 --> 19:37.934
AND DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I FEEL NOW?

19:37.934 --> 19:39.300
PAIN.

19:39.300 --> 19:42.233
IT'S LIKE MY HEART'S
BEEN RIPPED OUT
AND STEPPED ON!

19:42.233 --> 19:44.133
SO JUST
DO ME A FAVOR

19:44.133 --> 19:46.700
AND STAY OUT OF
MY PERSONAL LIFE,

19:46.700 --> 19:47.700
OK?

19:47.700 --> 19:49.467
SHAWN, I'M SORRY.

19:49.467 --> 19:51.000
I MEAN IT!

19:51.000 --> 19:52.600
I WILL.

19:52.600 --> 19:55.100
I MEAN IT.

19:57.667 --> 19:59.100
YOU ARE SO LUCKY

19:59.100 --> 20:00.700
THAT SOMEONE FOUND
YOUR PURSE.

20:00.700 --> 20:01.834
I KNOW.
I THOUGHT

20:01.834 --> 20:03.000
IT WAS GONE
FOREVER.

20:03.000 --> 20:05.233
WELL, HERE'S
ALL YOUR
STUFF BACK.

20:05.233 --> 20:06.233
GREAT.

20:06.233 --> 20:07.300
WAIT A MINUTE.

20:07.300 --> 20:09.233
ANGELA'S STUFF
WAS IN YOUR PURSE?

20:09.233 --> 20:10.734
YEAH. I LENT IT
TO HER.

20:10.734 --> 20:12.867
I FELT AWFUL
WHEN I LOST IT.

20:12.867 --> 20:15.367
<i>YOUR </i>STUFF WAS IN HER PURSE?

20:15.367 --> 20:17.400
THE LIP GLOSS,
THE SNO-CAPS?

20:17.400 --> 20:19.400
YEAH. AND MY BOOK
OF SONNETS.

20:19.400 --> 20:21.500
I CAN'T LIVE
WITHOUT THESE.

20:33.300 --> 20:35.967
Jack: MR. FEENY?
IT'S ME, JACK.

20:35.967 --> 20:37.700
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

20:37.700 --> 20:40.100
NOTHING.

20:40.100 --> 20:41.734
YOU NEED HELP
STUDYING, DON'T YOU?

20:41.734 --> 20:43.567
WHO, ME? NAH.

20:43.567 --> 20:45.400
COME ON IN.
COME ON IN.

20:45.400 --> 20:47.667
YOUR PRAYER'S
BEEN ANSWERED.

20:47.667 --> 20:48.700
COME ON.

20:48.700 --> 20:49.700
YOU?

20:49.700 --> 20:50.700
YEAH.

20:50.700 --> 20:52.200
OH, MAN, I WAS KINDA
HOPING FOR YOUR--

20:52.200 --> 20:56.467
YOUR MAGICAL,
INVISIBLE MR. FEENY
MENTOR GUY.

20:56.467 --> 20:58.600
OK, LISTEN. FIRST OF ALL,

20:58.600 --> 21:00.400
HE DOESN'T EXIST, OK?

21:00.400 --> 21:03.600
SECOND OF ALL, HE'S
IN LAUGHLIN, NEVADA.

21:03.600 --> 21:07.300
THIRD OF ALL, YOU'VE GOT
THE SKILLS, MY FRIEND.

21:07.300 --> 21:08.700
YOU JUST GOTTA USE 'EM.

21:08.700 --> 21:10.367
OK? TAKE A SEAT. COME ON.

21:10.367 --> 21:13.900
ALL RIGHT. I'M GONNA
SHOOT A QUESTION
OUT AT YOU NOW.

21:13.900 --> 21:15.133
OK.

21:15.133 --> 21:17.033
ALL RIGHT? YOU
READY? YOU SURE?
IT'S A TOUGH ONE.

21:17.033 --> 21:18.133
POE'S MAJOR WORK.

21:18.133 --> 21:19.300
GONNA GIVE YOU
A HINT:

21:19.300 --> 21:20.834
NEVERMORE.

21:23.867 --> 21:26.133
THIS IS CALCULUS.

21:30.200 --> 21:32.000
MR. FEENY.

21:33.400 --> 21:35.300
MR. FEENY!
